---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { FORA_APPROVED } from "../lib/advisor";

const title = "Terms of Service — Sky & Swim";
const description =
  "The terms that apply to your use of skyandswim.com, including editorial disclaimers, affiliate relationships, intellectual property, and limitations of liability.";
const lastUpdated = "July 22, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="legal">
    <div class="section-inner narrow">
      <header class="legal-head">
        <p class="kicker">Legal</p>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of
          <a class="inline-link" href="https://skyandswim.com/">skyandswim.com</a> (the
          "Site"), operated by <strong>Sunstate Bay Ventures, LLC</strong>, a Florida
          limited liability company doing business as Sky and Swim ("Sky &amp; Swim,"
          "we," "us," or "our"). By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these
          Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>1. What Sky &amp; Swim is</h2>
        <p>
          Sky &amp; Swim is a curated editorial directory of rooftop pool hotels
          across America. We research, review, and recommend properties based on
          independent editorial judgment.
          {!FORA_APPROVED && (
            <>
              {" "}We are <strong>not</strong> a travel agency, tour operator, online
              travel agency (OTA), or booking platform. We do not sell, book, confirm,
              or modify reservations. We do not handle payment for stays.
            </>
          )}
        </p>
        <p>
          When you click a booking link on the Site, you are taken to a third-party
          booking partner (such as Booking.com or a hotel's own website) where any
          booking, payment, and contractual relationship is solely between you and
          that third party, under their terms and policies.
        </p>
        {FORA_APPROVED && (
          <p>
            Separately, Sunstate Bay Ventures, LLC acts as an independent travel
            advisor affiliated with Fora Travel. Where you choose to book a stay
            through our advisory service rather than a booking link, your
            reservation, payment, and contractual relationship are governed by Fora
            and the applicable supplier (the hotel, hotel group, or their partners)
            under their terms and policies. Editorial inclusion in the directory and
            Editor's Picks is set independently of whether a property can be booked
            through our advisory service.
          </p>
        )}
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Editorial content</h2>
        <p>
          We work to keep information about hotels accurate and current, but the
          Site is provided for general informational purposes only. Hotels change
          ownership, renovate, modify amenities, close pools for the season, and
          update pricing without notice. Pool access, day-pass rules, hours, and
          other features described on the Site may differ from what is currently
          offered.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong
            >You are responsible for verifying all material details directly with
            the hotel or booking partner before booking and before traveling.</strong
          > This includes, but is not limited to, room type, pool access and hours,
          included amenities, seasonal closures, accessibility, and total cost.
          Editorial descriptions, "Editor's Picks," and similar designations reflect
          our opinion at the time of publication and are not guarantees of any
          specific experience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Affiliate &amp; advisor relationships</h2>
        <p>
          Sky &amp; Swim participates in affiliate programs. When you click certain
          booking links and complete a qualifying booking, we may earn a commission
          at no additional cost to you. Affiliate relationships do not influence
          which hotels appear in the directory or which receive an Editor's Pick —
          our editorial standards are set independently of commercial relationships.
        </p>
        {FORA_APPROVED && (
          <p>
            As an independent travel advisor affiliated with Fora Travel, we may
            also earn a commission from a hotel, hotel group, or supplier when you
            book a stay through our advisory service. This commission is paid by the
            supplier, not added to your rate. As with affiliate links, advisor
            commissions do not influence editorial inclusion, Editor's Picks, or the
            order in which properties are presented.
          </p>
        )}
        <p>
          We disclose these relationships in keeping with the U.S. Federal Trade
          Commission's guidance on endorsements. For details on data collected by
          affiliate partners, see our <a class="inline-link" href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. No travel advice</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing on the Site constitutes legal, medical, financial, or professional
          travel advice. Travel involves risk, including but not limited to risks
          related to health, safety, weather, and transportation. You are
          responsible for assessing those risks, obtaining appropriate insurance,
          and complying with applicable laws.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          The Site and its original content — including written reviews, "Editor's
          Picks" notes, editorial commentary, photographs taken by us, branding,
          logos, and the overall selection, arrangement, and presentation of hotels
          — are owned by Sunstate Bay Ventures, LLC and are protected by U.S. and
          international copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
        </p>
        <p>You may:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>View, browse, and personally use the Site for non-commercial purposes.</li>
          <li>Share links to individual pages on social media or in private messages.</li>
          <li>
            Quote brief excerpts (a sentence or two) with clear attribution and a
            link back to the source page.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>You may not:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Copy, scrape, republish, syndicate, or redistribute Site content in
            whole or in substantial part, in any medium, without our prior written
            permission.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use any automated system (including scrapers, bots, or AI training
            pipelines) to access, copy, or extract content from the Site.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use Sky &amp; Swim names, marks, logos, or branding except as expressly
            permitted in writing.
          </li>
          <li>Frame, mirror, or otherwise present the Site as your own.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Third-party content on the Site — including hotel photographs supplied by
          properties, booking partners, or photography sources, brand names, and
          logos — remains the property of its respective owners and is used under
          license, fair use, or with permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Site for any unlawful purpose or in violation of these Terms.</li>
          <li>
            Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Site, its servers, or related
            systems.
          </li>
          <li>
            Interfere with or disrupt the Site, introduce malware, or otherwise
            impair the experience of other users.
          </li>
          <li>
            Submit false, misleading, or fraudulent information through any contact
            form, email signup, or other input.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the Site to harvest personal information about other users or to
            send unsolicited communications.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Third-party sites and services</h2>
        <p>
          The Site links to third-party websites and services, including booking
          partners, affiliate networks, social media platforms, and other resources.
          We do not control those third parties and are not responsible for their
          content, policies, products, services, availability, or practices. Your
          interactions with any third-party site or service are governed by that
          third party's own terms and policies, and any transaction you enter into
          with a third party is solely between you and that third party.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          <strong
            >The Site and all content on it are provided on an "as is" and "as
            available" basis, without warranties of any kind, whether express or
            implied.</strong
          > To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, we disclaim all
          warranties, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability,
          fitness for a particular purpose, non-infringement, accuracy,
          completeness, reliability, availability, and uninterrupted operation.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not warrant that hotel descriptions, prices, availability,
          amenities, photos, or other information on the Site are accurate, current,
          or complete. We do not warrant that the Site will be free of errors,
          viruses, or interruptions. We do not endorse, guarantee, or assume
          responsibility for any product or service offered by any third party
          referenced on the Site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          <strong
            >To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, in no event shall
            Sunstate Bay Ventures, LLC, its members, officers, employees,
            contractors, or affiliates be liable for any indirect, incidental,
            special, consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for any loss
            of profits, revenue, data, goodwill, or other intangible losses, arising
            out of or related to your use of the Site, your inability to use the
            Site, or any content on the Site — whether based on warranty, contract,
            tort (including negligence), or any other legal theory, and whether or
            not we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.</strong
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong
            >In no event shall our total cumulative liability to you for all claims
            arising out of or related to the Site exceed one hundred U.S. dollars
            (US$100.00).</strong
          >
        </p>
        <p>
          We are not responsible for any aspect of your travel experience, including
          but not limited to issues with reservations, payments, refunds,
          accommodations, transportation, illness, injury, lost or damaged property,
          weather, natural disasters, or the acts or omissions of any hotel, booking
          partner, or other third party.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of certain
          warranties or damages. In those jurisdictions, our liability is limited to
          the fullest extent permitted by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Sunstate Bay Ventures,
          LLC and its members, officers, employees, contractors, and affiliates from
          and against any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses
          (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to: (a)
          your use of the Site; (b) your violation of these Terms; (c) your
          violation of any third-party right; or (d) any content you submit through
          the Site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Changes to the Site and these Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Site at any time
          without notice. We may also update these Terms from time to time. When we
          do, we will revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
          Material changes will be highlighted on the homepage or via our email
          list. Your continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
          acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may, in our sole discretion, restrict or terminate your access to the
          Site at any time, with or without notice, for any reason, including any
          violation of these Terms. Sections 5 (Intellectual Property), 8
          (Disclaimers), 9 (Limitation of Liability), 10 (Indemnification), 13
          (Governing Law and Disputes), and any other provisions that by their
          nature should survive will survive termination.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>13. Governing law and disputes</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida, without
          regard to its conflict-of-laws principles. You agree that any dispute,
          claim, or controversy arising out of or relating to these Terms or your
          use of the Site will be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts
          located in Pinellas County, Florida, and you consent to the personal
          jurisdiction of those courts.
        </p>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, you and Sky &amp; Swim
          each waive any right to a jury trial and any right to participate in a
          class action with respect to any such dispute.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>14. Severability and entire agreement</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these Terms is held to be invalid or unenforceable,
          the remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect. These
          Terms, together with the <a class="inline-link" href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>,
          constitute the entire agreement between you and Sky &amp; Swim regarding
          the Site and supersede any prior agreements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>15. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms can be sent to:</p>
        <p class="legal-contact">
          Sunstate Bay Ventures, LLC<br />
          d/b/a Sky and Swim<br />
          <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:hello@skyandswim.com">hello@skyandswim.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <Footer />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    display: block;
  }

  .narrow {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .legal-head {
    padding: clamp(7rem, 16vh, 10rem) 0 clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 10px rgba(3, 12, 28, 0.45);
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow:
      0 1px 2px rgba(3, 12, 28, 0.5),
      0 2px 18px rgba(3, 12, 28, 0.55);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(220, 240, 245, 0.7);
  }

  .legal section {
    padding: 1.4rem 0;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 14px rgba(3, 12, 28, 0.4);
  }

  .legal p,
  .legal li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(224, 241, 245, 0.9);
    text-shadow: 0 1px 12px rgba(3, 12, 28, 0.3);
  }

  .legal p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .legal ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(42, 191, 191, 0.4);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .inline-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--teal);
  }

  .legal-contact {
    background: rgba(5, 20, 40, 0.4);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--watermelon);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
